{"type":"message","id":"9244c8b1","parentId":"740a95ac","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:13:59.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the message tool with explicit target=8212808444 works fine. The cron jobs are using `delivery: { mode: \"announce\", channel: \"telegram\" }` without a `to` field, and the system is trying to resolve `@bobbygalletta` which fails.\n\nThe fix for the cron job would be to add `to: \"8212808444\"` explicitly to the delivery config. But the job is already created. Let me check if I can update the existing job or if I need to delete and recreate.\n\nActually wait - for the next run, I should update the job to include `to: \"8212808444\"` explicitly. Let me remove the old one and create a new one with explicit chat ID.","thinkingSignature":"9a7d377de113329aae101574a05b6c81a5f9eaeffbd7b0be89df3d9863d947ad"},{"type":"text","text":"That works! ✅ \n\nThe issue is my cron jobs use `announce` mode without a `to` field, and the system tries to resolve `@bobbygalletta` (fails). \n\nFixing the 8am reminder to explicitly target your chat ID:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k8kta22pudyh_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"remove","jobId":"480a61b7-9506-43e4-b42a-2209496eee12"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23567,"output":267,"cacheRead":19030,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42864,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774073632913}}
