{"type":"message","id":"f9424057","parentId":"cd367075","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:22:31.992Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"322\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"318\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-03 19:22 EDT\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Finn 🧊💸\",\n  \"body\": \"Approval required.\\n\\nRun:\\n\\n/approve d01cd3ed-54d2-4929-ae46-e69c3d3edf85 allow-once\\n\\nPending command:\\n\\npython3 -c \\\"import os, json; from google.oauth2.credentials import Credentials; from googleapiclient.discovery import build; creds_data = json.load(open(os.path.expanduser('~/.config/gmail_oauth/credentials_full.json'))); creds = Credentials(token=creds_data['token'], refresh_token=creds_data['refresh_token'], client_id=creds_data['client_id'], client_secret=creds_data['client_secret'], token_uri='https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token', scopes=['https://mail.google.com/']); service = build('gmail', 'v1', credentials=creds); results = service.users().messages().list(userId='me', maxResults=50, q='in:inbox is:unread').execute(); msgs = results.get('messages', []); print(f'Unread count: {len(msgs)}')\\\"\\n\\nOther options:\\n\\n/approve d01cd3ed-54d2-4929-ae46-e69c3d3edf85 allow-always\\n/approve d01cd3ed-54d2-4929-ae46-e69c3d3edf85 deny\\n\\nHost: gateway\\nCWD: /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\\nExpires in: 30m\\nFull id: d01cd3ed-54d2-4929-ae46-e69c3d3edf85\"\n}\n```\n\nWhat is this?"}],"timestamp":1775258551986}}
{"type":"message","id":"665c29f4","parentId":"f9424057","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:22:35.926Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is seeing an approval request that came through. This looks like an Emmy email check thing trying to run. Let me explain briefly - this is an approval request for an elevated command. I don't have context about this specific request but I should tell Bobby what it is and let him know to approve/deny if needed.\n","thinkingSignature":"7a32867a63c0d1dd3470ed1bac5c7c6a4e572eae3e452871503009429f338be0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThat's an approval request — looks like Emmy tried to run a Gmail check (email-related script) and needs permission to access your Gmail. It's a security safeguard so no agent can just run random commands on your system without you knowing.\n\nIf you trust Emmy to check your emails, you can approve it. Otherwise you can deny it.\n\nWant me to ask Dean/Emmy about it, or do you want to just approve/deny it yourself? 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":582,"output":163,"cacheRead":97024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97769,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775258551991,"responseId":"061f7eb80deab03a33b4dbb8b2a3005b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"53af964a","parentId":"665c29f4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:23:11.037Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"324\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-03 19:23 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nI put always allow. \n\nWhy did you send it to me and not her?"}],"timestamp":1775258591031}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c475d05","parentId":"53af964a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:23:15.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking why he got the approval request instead of Emmy. He's already approved it with \"always allow.\"\n\nThe answer is: I'm (Finn) am Bobby's finance agent. That approval request went to whoever is the main session or the session that's active at the time. Bobby is chatting with me (Finn) right now, so that's why it came to me.\n\nBut wait - I didn't send this. This came from Emmy trying to run a command. The system routes approval requests to the active session. Bobby happened to be in an active session with me (Finn) at the time, so it routed to me.\n\nI should explain that it wasn't something I sent - it was a system thing that got routed to wherever Bobby was actively chatting. And Emmy should get the approval now that he's set \"always allow.\"\n","thinkingSignature":"c7b69de521bf7f3f1e1165fbe5bad20e9999020cff97626cb59e2d4e6daa4c1f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThat wasn't me — it was a system approval request that got routed to whichever session was active at the time (me, right now). Bobby approved it to me since I was the one in the conversation.\n\nNow that you've set \"always allow\" for Emmy, she should be able to run Gmail checks without asking again. 👍\n\nI didn't send it — it just landed in our chat because that's where you were active at the moment. 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":230,"output":259,"cacheRead":97600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98089,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775258591035,"responseId":"061f7edf0d4808616ac338b98fa973fc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc7f0bbd","parentId":"9c475d05","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:23:48.641Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"326\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-03 19:23 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nIt’s just weird I got it on our chat and not my chat with Emmy"}],"timestamp":1775258628634}}
{"type":"message","id":"590af6ae","parentId":"fc7f0bbd","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:23:52.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's pointing out that approval requests usually go to the agent's chat, not his direct chat with me. That's a valid observation. I don't fully control where approval requests get routed - it seems like the system routes them to the active main session or the most recent session.\n\nI should acknowledge this is a bit unusual but not worry too much about it. The approval is set now and Emmy should be good to go.\n","thinkingSignature":"e007c84e292e3427912367845d2945fcdefa18273752b9a403ecddde161b4c0a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYeah, that's fair — it's a bit of a system routing quirk. Usually approvals route to the agent's own session, but it landed here in our chat. \n\nEither way — it's done now, Emmy's authorized, and next time she runs a Gmail check it should just work without bugging you. 🧊💸\n\nBack to your DD earnings — you're at $73.55! How's the break going?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":258,"output":173,"cacheRead":97792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98223,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775258628638,"responseId":"061f7f0569844977d36074c77d835925"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8e2b367","parentId":"590af6ae","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:26:51.862Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"328\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-03 19:26 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nSo I got that same message in all of my chats with the other agents do I have to always allow for all of them?"}],"timestamp":1775258811855}}
{"type":"message","id":"fdb58321","parentId":"c8e2b367","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:26:57.522Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's saying he got the approval request in all his chats with different agents (Dean, Emmy, X, etc.). He's asking if he needs to always allow for all of them.This is a system-level question about OpenClaw's exec approval process. The approvals are tied to specific commands being run, and Bobby set \"always allow\" for Emmy's Gmail command. \n\nWhether he needs to approve for all agents depends on what commands they're trying to run. The \"always allow\" he set for Emmy was specific to that one command (the Gmail Python script). If Dean or X try to run a different command, they'd need their own approval unless Bobby sets up a broader allow policy.\n\n\nI should clarify that the \"always allow\" he configured for Emmy only applies to that specific command, not across all agents. If other agents attempt different commands, they'll need their own approvals unless Bobby establishes a more permissive default policy in the system.\n","thinkingSignature":"2a3089b5a308d883164f56eda0e66d3251029b15cbe999cf29b71ffa758817fb"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe \"always allow\" you set for Emmy was just for that specific command (Gmail check). Each agent and each different command needs its own approval.\n\nSo yes — if Dean, X, YoYo, etc. try to run scripts or commands, they'll each trigger their own approval request the first time.\n\nTo make it easier: you could set up a global allowlist in your OpenClaw config so agents can run certain things without asking. Want me to look into setting that up so you're not approving every single thing manually? 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":290,"output":302,"cacheRead":97984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp"