{"type":"message","id":"7f685853","parentId":"0db60505","timestamp":"2026-04-04T15:59:01.798Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to:1. Flag the DoorDash gas starting TODAY (April 4)\n2. For April 1-3, he doesn't want to flag the gas because he wasn't tracking properly and his tank was full at the beginning of April\n\nSo basically he's saying:- April 1-3 gas purchases: Don't categorize them as DoorDash or personal — just leave them as-is for now since he wasn't tracking\n- From April 4 onward: Flag DoorDash gas separately\n\nLet me update the tracker to:\n1. Remove the gas categorization from the April 2 items (Kroger Gas, Casey's) — just leave them as \"Gas\" without the DoorDash flag for those old entries\n2. Create a new format for going forward where DoorDash gas is flagged\n\n\n3. Wait, but those gas purchases ($43.90 and $22.06) total $65.96, which is significant. And he hit his $147 goal on April 2 and 3, so that gas money did come from DD earnings.\n\nActually, re-reading what he said — he wants to START flagging DoorDash gas TODAY (April 4). So the April 1-3 gas purchases shouldn't be flagged as DoorDash gas, they should just stay as regular transactions since he wasn't tracking then. The fresh tank at the start of April complicates this, but I should respect his ask to start fresh from today.\n\nSo I'll update the tracker: remove the DoorDash flag from those older gas entries and instead create two categories going forward — \"DoorDash Gas\" for business expenses and \"Personal Gas\" for non-DD driving. Then I can calculate what he's owed based on how many DD days he's worked since April 1. the DOORDASH portion from that total. Since he filled up at the start of April and can't remember what was DD vs personal, it's cleaner to just treat April 1-3 as untracked and start fresh today. I'll update the file to reflect this and note that going forward, DoorDash gas gets separated out.\n","thinkingSignature":"cce