{"type":"message","id":"a2df122f","parentId":"3df5f54b","timestamp":"2026-04-04T16:03:59.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Oh I misread - Bobby hasn't paid any bills yet because none were actually due yet on April 4. Let me think about what bills have actually come due up to today (April 4):- April 1: Xfinity $118 - that was due April 1, so it's now past due!\n- April 2: Affirm Marriott $129.59 - due April 2, past due\n- April 3: KUB $362.20 - due April 3, past due\n\nSo actually April 1, 2, and 3 bills ARE past due now (today is April 4). \n\nBut Bobby said \"up until today, I haven't paid anything that was due yet\" - so he knows these are past due but hasn't paid them. He wants to know what his actual cash position is considering these unpaid bills.\n\n\nActually wait - if the total bills including the past due ones is $1,556.17 and he has $1,016.33 cash, then he's already short by $539.84 right now. So he's facing a serious cash flow problem before we even get to the remaining bills on April 8 and beyond.\n","thinkingSignature":"510594e35194edcde215c32a54ae5069073618f2344bfb51245448bed1f7d8c8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOh gotcha — so you're asking about what's actually past due right now (not what you owe in total):\n\n| Past Due | Bill | Amount |\n|----------|------|--------|\n| Apr 1 | Xfinity Internet | $118.00 |\n| Apr 2 | Affirm - Marriott Hotels | $129.59 |\n| Apr 3 | KUB (old apartment) | $362.20 |\n\n**Past due total: $609.79**\n\n**$1,016.33 - $609.79 = $406.54**\n\nAfter paying those 3 past due bills, you'd have **$406.54** left.\n\nThat's still positive but tight. The rest of the April bills ($946.38) come due later and you have DD income + Logan's paycheck (Apr 7) coming to cover those. 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":565,"output":416,"cacheRead":110336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111317,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache