{"type":"message","id":"5583a48a","parentId":"884d5901","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:23:44.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me summarize Bobby's DD earnings vs goals from the beginning of April:\n\n**Daily tracker:**\n- April 1: $119.13 / $125 goal = -$5.87 (but he changed goal to $147 from April 2)\n- April 2: $159.91 / $147 goal = +$12.91\n- April 3: $147.06 / $147 goal = +$0.06\n- April 4: No DD (brakes/Easter)\n- April 5: No DD (brakes/Easter)\n- April 6: $148.65 / $147 goal = +$1.65\n- April 7: $123.61 + $15 reimbursement = $138.61 / $147 goal = -$8.39\n- April 8: $120.40 / $148.20 goal = -$27.80\n\n**Running total:**\nApril 1 short: $5.87 (used $125 base)\nApril 2: +$12.91\nApril 3: +$0.06\nApril 6: +$1.65\nApril 7: -$8.39 (actually $123.61 + $15 = $138.61)\nApril 8: -$27.80\n\nApril 1 shortfall: $5.87\nApril 2-6 surplus: +$12.91 + $0.06 + $1.65 = +$14.62\nApril 7 shortfall: -$8.39\nApril 8 shortfall: -$27.80\n\nNet since April 1 (excluding no-DD days): +$14.62 - $5.87 - $8.39 - $27.80 = -$27.44\n\nWait let me recalculate. Bobby changed the goal starting April 2 to $147. \n\nSo April 1 was based on $125 goal, April 2 onward based on $147. Let me redo the running total:\n- April 1: $119.13 vs $125 goal = -$5.87\n- April 2: $159.91 vs $147 goal = +$12.91\n- April 3: $147.06 vs $147 goal = +$0.06\n- April 6: $148.65 vs $147 goal = +$1.65\n- April 7: $138.61 vs $147 goal = -$8.39\n- April 8: $120.40 vs $148.20 goal = -$27.80\n\nCumulative: -$5.87 + $12.91 + $0.06 + $1.65 - $8.39 - $27.80 = -$27.44\n\nNow looking at April 1 more carefully since he didn't reach the $125 goal: $119.13 vs $125 = -$5.87. And then April 7 was short by $8.39 (he made $123.61 plus the $15 reimbursement bringing it to $138.61 versus the $147 target). April 8 was a bigger miss at $120.40 against $148.20.\n\nSo for April 1 to April 8, the total shortfall is $42.06 when I add those three misses together, though some of this gets offset by the gains on April 2, 3, and 6.","thinkingSignature":"e0106859161ce2cdc2b12a672a4e4e69c00201cc1834aee1b2cb80c3ef3517f6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's the full picture from April 1-8:\n\n| Day | Earnings | Goal | Surplus/Short |\n|-----|----------|------|---------------|\n| Apr 1 | $119.13 | $125.00 | **-$5.87** |\n| Apr 2 | $159.91 | $147.00 | **+$12.91** |\n| Apr 3 | $147.06 | $147.00 | **+$0.06** |\n| Apr 4-5 | $0 | — | DD off (brakes) |\n| Apr 6 | $148.65 | $147.00 | **+$1.65** |\n| Apr 7 | $138.61 | $147.00 | **-$8.39** |\n| Apr 8 | $120.40 | $148.20 | **-$27.80** |\n\n**Running total: -$27.44**\n\nSo yes — Apr 2, 3, and 6 you hit goal. But Apr 1, 7, and 8 you fell short. Net shortfall of $27.44.\n\nGoing forward: $153/day for 7 days catches you up AND puts you $5.81 ahead by Apr 15! 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":105838,"output":977,"cacheRead":16896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123711,"cost":{"input":0.0317514,"output":0.0011723999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0010137599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03393756}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775701394060,"responseId":"0626409269dbab9d69e95ff7a47a0cba"}}
