{"type":"message","id":"ef91b634","parentId":"2d8a11fd","timestamp":"2026-04-10T15:39:16.593Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"515\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-10 11:39 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nI have come bonds I can cash as well even though they aren’t fully mature yet"}],"timestamp":1775835556588}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0eac88f","parentId":"ef91b634","timestamp":"2026-04-10T15:39:28.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby has savings bonds that he can cash in, even though they're not fully mature. This could be a source of cash to help with the move. I should ask how much they're worth (face value) and how much he'd get if he cashed them now vs waiting for maturity.","thinkingSignature":"07bfdb8eef5769a453f7c5813c0d0d21612e358f8b2cf3a2cc5f55833b7dd1fe"},{"type":"text","text":"Smart thinking! \n\nHow much are they worth (face value)? And do you know how much you'd get if you cashed them now vs waiting for maturity?\n\nSavings bonds are great because they're basically free money — but if you need the cash now, early redemption is better than borrowing.\n\nLet me know the numbers and we can factor that into the plan! 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98,"output":138,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":148826,"totalTokens":149062,"cost":{"input":0.0000294,"output":0.0001656,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.05580975,"total":0.05600475}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775835556593,"responseId":"06284ca4be906dcc24b1aae2fedc0ef2"}}
