{"type":"message","id":"d18a75a4","parentId":"e17b420c","timestamp":"2026-04-11T04:31:59.380Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's right to correct me. I was looking at static cash without adding DD earnings.\n\nLet me recalculate properly with DD earnings:\n\nStarting cash: $1,232.71\n\nIf he DD at $164/day and earns consistently:\n- Apr 11-30 = 20 days × $164 = $3,280 in DD earnings\n\nSo:\nStarting: $1,232.71\n+ DD earnings (20 days): +$3,280\n- Bills: -$888.58\n\n= $3,624.13 by end of April\n\nThe LOWEST point would be right before big bills are paid, but with DD income coming in daily, he'd be replenishing.\n\nLet me track day by day:\n- Apr 11: +$164 - $25.74 = $1,370.97\n- Apr 12: +$164 - $29.87 = $1,505.10\n- Apr 13-14: +$328 = $1,833.10\n- Apr 15: +$164 - $237.25 = $1,759.85\n- Apr 16-20: +$656 = $2,415.85\n- Apr 21: +$164 - $18 + $500 (Logan paycheck) = $3,061.85\n- Apr 22-26: +$656 = $3,717.85\n- Apr 27: +$164 - $424.41 = $3,457.44\n- Apr 28: +$164 - $74 = $3,547.44\n- Apr 29-30: +$328 = $3,875.44\n\nWait, the bills are being paid as they come due, not all at once. So daily cash flow:\n\n\n- Apr 11: Start $1,232.71 + $164 - $25.74 = $1,370.97\n- Apr 12: +$164 - $29.87 = $1,505.10\n- Apr 13: +$164 = $1,669.10\n- Apr 14: +$164 = $1,833.10\n- Apr 15: +$164 - $237.25 = $1,759.85\n- Apr 16: +$164 = $1,923.85\n- Apr 17: +$164 - $15.31 = $2,072.54\n- Apr 18: +$164 = $2,236.54\n- Apr 19: +$164 = $2,400.54\n- Apr 20: +$164 = $2,564.54\n- Apr 21: +$164 - $18 + $500 = $3,210.54\n- Apr 22: +$164 = $3,374.54\n- Apr 23: +$164 = $3,538.54\n- Apr 24: +$164 = $3,702.54\n- Apr 25: +$164 = $3,866.54\n- Apr 26: +$164 = $4,030.54\n- Apr 27: +$164 - $424.41 = $3,770.13\n- Apr 28: +$164 - $74 = $3,860.13\n- Apr 29: +$164 = $4,024.13\n- Apr 30: +$164 - $64 = $4,124.13\n\nThe lowest cash balance hits around mid-April at roughly $1,370, which is significantly higher than my initial $50-100 estimate. Bobby's concern was justified.","think