{"type":"message","id":"787755cc","parentId":"24e938a0","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.017Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - my finances-update-reminder-930pm job (fa592c4d-307c-4c45-b792-06061622e405) is gone. It was a deleteAfterRun one-shot, so it probably fired and either deleted itself on success, or errored out and was removed. But wait, the list doesn't show it anymore. Let me look at the X cleanup reminder - it shows lastRunStatus: \"error\" with \"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed\". That's X's agent having issues.\n\nMy reminder job is just gone from the list. Since it had deleteAfterRun: true, maybe it was deleted after it ran (even on error?). Or maybe it never fired at all.\n\n\nThe 9:30pm cron for X shows a message failure, but that's X's job, not mine. My finances reminder with deleteAfterRun might have fired and errored out, which would explain why it's gone from the list. Or it could still be sitting there with a status I can't see. Either way, I need to set up a new job for 8am tomorrow and investigate what went wrong.","thinkingSignature":"979de1810daa28dfa62871a91b1a3057d2f32a153c193088fd5222e5a326c1b0"},{"type":"text","text":"My reminder job is gone from the list — looks like it may have fired and errored out (then deleted itself since it was a one-shot). The message failed, so I never reached you.\n\nSetting it back up for **8am tomorrow**:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dwo7cspfu3zf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"date -v+1d +%Y-%m-%d"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20681,"output":323,"cacheRead":19030,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40034,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774073586149}}
