{"type":"message","id":"f336cd10","parentId":"45b6998d","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.017Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now. There are two types of errors:\n\n1. `sendMessage failed: Network request for 'sendMessage' failed!` - Network issues\n2. `Telegram recipient @bobbygalletta could not be resolved to a numeric chat ID` - The Telegram target @bobbygalletta can't be resolved\n\nThe X agent is trying to send to `@bobbygalletta` which doesn't work - it needs the numeric chat ID `8212808444`. \n\nBut my cron job uses `delivery: { mode: \"announce\", channel: \"telegram\" }` with no explicit `to`. It should use the session's default recipient. But the error at 21:30 shows `@bobbygalletta` - so some job is trying to send to that username and failing.\n \nI'm realizing the announce delivery mode might not be using the configured Telegram bot's default chat, or the isolated session doesn't have access to that context. Looking at the session key `agent:finn:telegram:direct:8212808444`, it should know the chat ID, but the error shows it's trying to resolve `@bobbygalletta` instead of using the numeric ID.\n\nFor the 8am reminder, I could bypass the announcement system entirely and use the message tool directly with the numeric chat ID, or better yet, just fire the cron job now since I'm actively talking to Bobby anyway.","thinkingSignature":"bdf5d1aa833d3a85841e86073de59644fcb95d8130ff3f5e5d096a57e78c71d8"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Ah, I see the problem — the gateway is failing to send to `@bobbygalletta` (username doesn't resolve). My isolated jobs use announce mode which tries to route through the bot, but the bot can't find that username.\n\nHere's the fix — let me try sending you a test right now to confirm the Telegram connection is working:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q3gl4eyn5bmg_1","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"telegram","target":"8212808444"