{"type":"message","id":"e6632c83","parentId":"4da0c61b","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.021Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b6icnuaskq5r_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 1149 more characters truncat"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":17,"aggregated":"Got **14 confirmed OpenClaw transcripts** saved to RexVideos. The master guide is ready.\n\n**Quick hits from what I can see:**\n\n🔑 **Top 3 things to implement:**\n1. **Set up morning brief via Telegram** — easiest win for immediate value\n2. **Create second brain** — replaces a bunch of apps with conversational interface\n3. **Reverse prompting** — ask OpenClaw \"what should we build?\" instead of telling it how\n\n🧠 **Key mindset shift:**\nTreat OpenClaw like a human employee, not a chatbot. It's smarter than you at *execution* — you provide the *what*, it figures out the *how*.\n\n📊 **Note on videos:** 14 transcripts confirmed (not 19). Some of Alex's content was posted as X videos instead of YouTube, and a few pages didn't load through web fetch. Still a solid amount of content to work with.\n\n**Everything is at:**\n`~/Desktop/RexVideos/AlexFinnOpenClaw/MasterOpenClawSetupGuide.md`\n\nWant me to read through the full guide and give you the highlights?\n2026-03-21T23:40:36.188-04:00 [ws] ⇄ res ✓ node.invoke 325ms conn=3a9d26a6…b016 id=215fab57…6e45\n2026-03-21T23:40:39.977-04:00 [ws] ⇄ res ✓ node.invoke 317ms conn=de867ad3…6d8c id=4857f220…2b2b","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-finn"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774150985050}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bf1a90b","parentId":"e6632c83","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.021Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log is mostly from other sessions. I don't see a clear entry for my finances-tonight-10pm job.\n\nOK so my job fired at 10pm, the isolated session ran, but the message wasn't delivered. The gateway log doesn't show it clearly because the session may have been handled differently. The job ran and deleted itself, but the announcement didn't make it to Bobby.\n\nI think the issue might be that even with `to: \"8212808444\"` in delivery, the isolated session's message tool call might have the wrong target. Looking at the job payload - it uses `agentTurn` which spins up an isolated session, and the delivery should announce to Telegram with the correct chat ID. But something went wrong.\n \nRather than keep debugging why the first job failed, I should just send Bobby the message directly right now and schedule another reminder for tomorrow at 3pm as backup.","thinkingSignature":"3eb112559662dc8147db45c3409c4050bca26d5745cf67f32a68f2b97c2875ef"},{"type":"text","text":"Yeah that 10pm one fired and deleted itself but you never got the message — something went wrong in the isolated session delivery. My bad.\n\nNudging you RIGHT NOW:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dtjc1uf7oqjf_1","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"telegram","target":"8212808444","message":"Hey Bobby! 👋 Still owe me those updated finances. No rush, just whenever you get a sec 🧊💸"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39199,"output":302,"cacheRead":20228,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59729,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774150985061}}
