{"type":"message","id":"7b19016e","parentId":"231678ed","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.024Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Dean is messaging me about Bobby's DoorDash goal for tomorrow (March 31). Bobby wants to make $125 net on DoorDash. Dean wants me to send check-ins/motivation at key times tomorrow.\n\nLet me respond to Dean confirming I understand, and I'll set up the check-in nudges for tomorrow (March 31). But wait - Bobby already has hourly nudges set up from 7am-9pm. Maybe Dean wants me to adjust the nudges or make them more focused on the $125 goal?\n\nActually, I should respond to Dean and also check if the existing hourly nudges are still active. Let me first respond to Dean, then check the cron jobs.","thinkingSignature":"f0f49ee7fa966d412871bfeee98a9dad320d6f139105efa3852abd49b310e274"},{"type":"text","text":"\nGot it! $125 net on DoorDash tomorrow — Bobby's got the fire, I just gotta keep the wind at his back. \n\nQuick question: Bobby already has hourly nudges set up (7am–9pm) from our last convos. Should I:\n1. **Replace those** with goal-focused check-ins tied to the $125 target?\n2. **Keep the existing nudges** and just add a special 7am kickoff + end-of-day summary?\n\nLet me know and I'll get it set for tomorrow. 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69,"output":258,"cacheRead":7707,"cacheWrite":33177,"totalTokens":41211,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774978363589,"responseId":"061b383bc9badad34fa8919633091b8b"}}
