ey'd theoretically have $2,232.73 by April 10. The $737 difference largely comes down to those two days without DD income.\n\nBobby's actually in a reasonably similar position to what was projected—the gap isn't about losing money, it's just that he hasn't earned as much as the calendar anticipated. They've covered all their past-due bills and have some breathing room, so they're managing the situation despite the missed days.","thinkingSignature":"e399b4fe3e54c7b40bca497b4adaa19e4197b860f4c51a7ad33539222d2afca8"},{"type":"text","text":"\nRough math:\n\n**Your cash:** ~$1,495.05\n**Bills remaining:** ~$888.58\n**After bills:** ~$606.47\n\n**Calendar projected for Apr 10:** $2,232.73\n\nSo actually you're **~$1,626 behind the calendar** — but that's mostly because you took 2 days off (Apr 4-5) for brakes and had some shortfalls.\n\nYou're not LOSING money — you're just EARNING less than projected. The calendar assumed $125/day every day, and you missed 2 full days + had shortfalls on others.\n\nWith the $164/day goal going forward, you'll close that gap. You're doing okay Bobby! 💪🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98,"output":671,"cacheRead":133365,"cacheWrite":1040,"totalTokens":135174,"cost":{"input":0.0000294,"output":0.0008052,"cacheRead":0.0080019,"cacheWrite":0.00039,"total":0.009226499999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775795331733,"responseId":"0627af83b09b897703d863ee66b42d74"}}
