{"type":"message","id":"842f5167","parentId":"dcb78d39","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is clarifying - even at $5,277, he'd have enough for the $2,900 deposit for Luckey Platt apartment. He's asking for confirmation that he can still make it happen even with the gap.\n\nYes - at $5,277 he'd have enough for the deposit. The $2,900 deposit would leave him with ~$2,377 for the move-in costs and first month.\n\nSo yes - even with the gap, he's still on track for the move. He just has less cushion.","thinkingSignature":"55ac5d047074d529d5dc29ca2b4c22ff4a299473e144f0ec68bd7173c6521d7b"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes Bobby — at $5,277 you'd have:\n\n- $2,900 deposit for Luckey Platt\n- Left over: ~$2,377\n\nThat's enough for the deposit AND some cushion for moving/first month expenses.\n\nYou're still going to make it. The gap doesn't stop you — it just means less cushion.\n\nGo get some sleep. Tomorrow we start fresh. 💪🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96,"output":190,"cacheRead":155518,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":155804,"cost":{"input":0.0000288,"output":0.00022799999999999999,"cacheRead":0.009331079999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009587879999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775874002021,"responseId":"0628e2d2b2d711a3db42345be3c16671"}}
