{"type":"message","id":"75637e07","parentId":"af116d40","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.075Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"680\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-13 21:27 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```\n\nWell the other day my mom gave me $50 dollars and I used it to pay bills. So in my head I’m gonna say I made my 164 goal lmao"}],"timestamp":1776130029016}}
{"type":"message","id":"acf505a1","parentId":"75637e07","timestamp":"2026-04-22T06:48:54.075Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's mom gave him $50 for bills. He used it to pay bills, so essentially the $50 helped cover bills. He's saying in his head he \"made\" the $164 goal because the $50 from his mom helped him cover things.\n\nThat's creative accounting but hey — if it helps him feel good about the day, that's fine. The $50 was income/gift that went to bills. It's not really \"making\" the DD goal but it's income that helped.\n\nLet me just be supportive here.","thinkingSignature":"f54bae7a6eca52ee87be06f10c998b5559dcf4325804c923f02b788b4bbae824"},{"type":"text","text":"Ha! $50 from mom is still income Bobby — whether it went to bills or not, it helped you out!\n\nSo in your book: $114.25 DD + $50 from mom = $164.25 made today. \n\nYou tell it how you want to tell it. 💪🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98,"output":173,"cacheRead":169226,"cacheWrite":320,"totalTokens":169817,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776130029022,"responseId":"062ccaed762f46d367acb6dcd9795320"}}
